Wash and dry produce. Slice @prosciutto{2%oz} in half crosswise. Cut
@fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into ¼-inch-thick slices. Thinly slice @tomato{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds; season with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @cashews{1/2%oz}, @pepitas{1/2%oz}, and @dried cranberries{1%oz}.

Toast @sourdough bread{2%slice} until golden; halve on a diagonal.

Divide toasted sourdough between plates. On the side, layer slices of
prosciutto, mozzarella, and tomato; drizzle with as much @balsamic glaze{5%tsp} as you like. Divide trail mix between #small bowls{} and serve alongside.